korean:
  title: 서회
  author: 김굉필
  language: kor
  text: |-
    한가히 홀로 있어 오고 감이 끊이고는
    다만 밝은 달 불러 차고 외로움 비치었네
    그대는 아예 이 생애를 묻지 마오
    두어 이랑 연파에 몇 첩의 청산뿐이로다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0370&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Reflections of the Heart
  author: Kim Hong-pil
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In solitude I dwell, where visits cease and comings go—
    I call upon the bright moon to cast its light on my cold loneliness.
    I beg you, ask me nothing of how I pass my days.
    Just a few acres of mist-rippled water, a handful of layered green mountains.
  footnotes:
    - The poem employs the traditional motif of withdrawal into nature as a spiritual refuge, a common theme in Korean Neo-Confucian literati culture.
    - The 'mist-rippled water' and 'layered mountains' represent both the physical landscape and the poet's inner landscape of solitude and contemplation.
